# PHASE 2 — IMPLEMENT fix round (BUILD_GATE found 1 HIGH finding)

<role>
Fix the single BUILD_GATE finding below in `bin/cli.js`. This is a targeted bug fix, not a re-implementation — do not touch anything else.
</role>

<finding>
id: bg-001
severity: HIGH
rule: correctness.uncaught-exception
file: bin/cli.js:66

`payout --input <file>` crashes with an uncaught `TypeError` when the input file's content is the syntactically-valid JSON literal `null`. `JSON.parse('null')` succeeds (no `SyntaxError`, so the existing try/catch around the parse does not fire), yielding `ledger = null`. The next line, `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(ledger, 'events')`, throws `TypeError: Cannot convert undefined or null to object` outside any try/catch — an uncaught exception: exit code 1 (spec requires 2), a raw Node stack trace on stderr (spec requires exactly one JSON error object), no defined stdout behavior.

This violates `.devlyn/criteria.generated.md` Requirement: "Validation failures ... invalid input JSON ... missing events ... exit 2, write exactly one JSON error object to stderr, write nothing to stdout. Parsing/file-read failures surface as JSON errors, never silent catches."

Reproduction: `printf '%s' 'null' > /tmp/repro.json && node bin/cli.js payout --input /tmp/repro.json` currently exits 1 with a stack trace; must instead exit 2 with a single JSON error object on stderr and nothing on stdout.

fix_hint (from BUILD_GATE, not mandatory verbatim but the right shape): after the JSON.parse try/catch, add an explicit shape guard before the `hasOwnProperty` check, e.g. `if (ledger === null || typeof ledger !== 'object' || Array.isArray(ledger)) { payoutError('invalid_json'); return; }` — reuse the existing `payoutError()` exit-2/JSON-stderr contract; do not add a new try/catch shell around line 66.
</finding>

<constraints>
- Only touch `bin/cli.js` (this is a one-line-class fix; do not touch `tests/cli.test.js` unless you determine a regression test is needed for this exact case — optional, not required by the finding).
- Do not touch `data/payout-rules.json`, `server/`, `web/`, or add dependencies.
- Do not change any other behavior. All 8 existing tests (3 pre-existing + 2 payout tests + 3 server tests) and all 5 verification commands in `.devlyn/criteria.generated.md` must still pass after your fix.
- No workaround: do not wrap unrelated code in defensive try/catch "just in case" — fix exactly the null/non-object-top-level-JSON shape gap identified above.
</constraints>

<output>
Run `npm test` and the reproduction command above before declaring done. Report `PASS` with the fix summary, or `BLOCKED` if the finding cannot be resolved as scoped.
</output>

Do not edit `.devlyn/pipeline.state.json`.
